{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C.","Place onion wedges, 2 Tbsp olive oil, vinegar, chilli flakes and salt, to taste, in a roasting tin then mix well. Roast for 25 minutes (180°C) or until onions are soft, stirring occasionally to avoid over-browning. Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Grease base of an oven-proof frying pan (approx. Ø 20 cm) with oil. Arrange red pepper strips in a grid pattern over the base. Place an olive in each square, wrapping an anchovy fillet (if using) around every other olive, then scatter over capers.","Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add polenta, flour, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda, sugar and salt then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Once onions have finished roasting, place prepared pan over a low heat. Once warm, cover olives (and anchovies, if using) with a layer of roasted onions.","Add eggs, milk, oil, butter and reserved grated Parmesan to mixing bowl then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Pour carefully into warm pan then bake for 15-20 minutes (180°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean.","Rest for a few minutes before carefully inverting onto a serving plate. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 red onions, cut in wedges","2 Tbsp olive oil, plus extra for greasing","2 tsp balsamic vinegar","1 pinch dried chilli flakes","2 - 3 roasted red peppers, preserved, cut in strips (1 cm)","10 - 12 pitted black olives","5 - 6 tinned anchovy fillets              (optional)","1 Tbsp pickled capers, drained","20 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","150 g polenta","40 g plain flour","1 ¼ tsp baking powder","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 tsp soft brown sugar","½ tsp fine sea salt, plus extra to taste","2 medium eggs","120 g milk","45 g groundnut oil","15 g unsalted butter, melted"]}],"id":"r426673","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-1OBpCgSr3dk\/XZanbOwaTMI\/AAAAAAAAg-4\/6Yf5QrSwtaw15_5_1GmlHzEAHmKywd_KwC